{
  "texts": [
    "The quality assessment of slides by technical assistants and pathologists is an integral component of the standard operating procedure of accredited pathology institutions 38.",
    "In clinical settings, when a slide is not suitable for pathological evaluation, a better slide is prepared from the same tissue block (prostatectomy specimens are embedded in blocks) for pathological evaluation.",
    "We anticipate that similar standards for image quality assessment will become routine in future digital pathology workflows.",
    "However, the implementation of a quality management system for histology slides in a clinical setting is beyond the scope of the current study.",
    "We consequently refer the reader to the relevant literature."
  ]
}